title: Smart Dataset Creator
description: Use AI technology to automatically generate high-quality training datasets from raw data, supporting multiple dataset types and formats.

qaPairs.name: QA Pairs
qaPairs.description: Generate question-answer pairs from document content, suitable for QA system training
qaPairs.useCase: Smart customer service, knowledge Q&A, educational assistance

instructionTuning.name: Instruction Tuning
instructionTuning.description: Generate instruction-input-output triplets for instruction-following model training
instructionTuning.useCase: Smart office, document processing, personalized assistant

textClassification.name: Text Classification
textClassification.description: Extract document fragments and generate classification labels for sentiment analysis, content moderation, etc.
textClassification.useCase: Sentiment analysis, content moderation, news classification, intent recognition

dialogue.name: Dialogue Tuning
dialogue.description: Generate multi-turn dialogue data to improve dialogue coherence and context understanding
dialogue.useCase: Smart customer service, chatbots, voice assistants

domainAdaptation.name: Domain Adaptation
domainAdaptation.description: Domain-specific knowledge fine-tuning to improve model performance in professional fields
domainAdaptation.useCase: Medical diagnosis, legal consultation, financial analysis

reasoning.name: Reasoning Tuning
reasoning.description: Reasoning data with chain of thought to train model logical reasoning abilities
reasoning.useCase: Math problem solving, code generation, logical reasoning, complex analysis

knowledgeDistillation.name: Knowledge Distillation
knowledgeDistillation.description: Extract knowledge from large models to train smaller models, balancing performance and cost
knowledgeDistillation.useCase: Model compression, edge deployment, cost optimization

alpaca.name: Alpaca Format
alpaca.description: Classic instruction tuning format released by Stanford University, simple structure, suitable for single-turn tasks

shareGPT.name: ShareGPT Format
shareGPT.description: Format supporting multi-turn dialogue and tool calling, closer to real interaction scenarios

openAI.name: OpenAI Format
openAI.description: OpenAI API compatible format, simplified version of ShareGPT

alpacaCOT.name: Alpaca-COT Format
alpacaCOT.description: Alpaca format with chain of thought, suitable for reasoning task training

csv.name: CSV Format
csv.description: Simple table format, suitable for classification and annotation tasks

configModel.name: Configure Model
configModel.description: Configure AI model and processing parameters

prompt.consistencyNote: Please ensure the generated data is consistent with project objectives.
prompt.strictFormatOutput: Please strictly follow the specified format for data output.
prompt.accuracy: Accuracy: Ensure extracted information is accurate and error-free, do not add content that does not exist in the document
prompt.completeness: Completeness: Cover key information points in the document, avoid missing important content
prompt.diversity: Diversity: Generate training samples of different types and difficulty levels
prompt.consistency: Consistency: Maintain consistency and standardization of data formats
prompt.relevance: Relevance: Ensure generated data is highly relevant to {{useCase}} scenarios
prompt.documentUnderstanding: Document Understanding: Deep understanding of document content and structure
prompt.intelligentExtraction: Intelligent Extraction: Identify key information and concepts
prompt.formatConversion: Format Conversion: Convert content to {{format}} format
prompt.qualityValidation: Quality Validation: Ensure each data item meets quality standards
prompt.structurePreservation: Structure Preservation: Prioritize maintaining the original structure of the document (titles, paragraphs, lists, etc.)
prompt.headerSplitting: Header Splitting: Prioritize splitting documents at markdown headers
prompt.shardProcessing: Shard Processing: The document will be divided into approximately {{totalChunks}} segments, please ensure each segment can generate valuable training data
prompt.finalInstruction: Please process each document segment one by one, generating the corresponding amount of high-quality training data for each segment. Ensure all generated data strictly follows {{format}} format specifications and reflects the characteristics of {{datasetType}}.

qaGuide.title: Q&A Pair Generation Guide
qaGuide.hierarchicalQuestions: Hierarchical Questions: Include factual, comprehension, application, analytical, and creative questions covering multiple levels of Bloom's taxonomy
qaGuide.naturalLanguage: Natural Language: Use natural, conversational question expressions that mimic real user questioning habits
qaGuide.clearDirection: Clear Direction: Each question should have a clear answer direction, avoiding vague or overly open-ended questions
qaGuide.practicality: Practicality: Questions should be those users might ask in real scenarios, with practical significance
qaGuide.diversityDepth: Diversity & Depth: Cover different difficulty levels, from basic cognition to deep analysis, ensuring data richness
qaGuide.accurateComplete: Accurate & Complete: Provide accurate, complete answers based on document content, do not fabricate information
qaGuide.clearStructure: Clear Structure: Use appropriate paragraphs, bullet points, and logical structure to organize answers
qaGuide.appropriateDepth: Appropriate Depth: Include necessary details while maintaining conciseness and clarity, avoiding redundancy
qaGuide.contextRelevant: Context Relevant: Answers should be closely related to questions and document context
qaGuide.professionalTone: Professional Tone: Maintain professional, friendly tone that reflects professional knowledge level
qaGuide.quantityPerChunk: Generate 5-8 high-quality Q&A pairs per document segment, ensuring full utilization of content
qaGuide.keyPointCoverage: Cover main information points in segments, including core concepts, key details, and practical information
qaGuide.appropriateDiversity: Ensure appropriate diversity among Q&A pairs, avoiding repetition or excessive similarity
qaGuide.difficultyGradient: Include questions of different difficulty gradients, from simple to complex in progression
qaGuide.practicalApplication: Combine with practical application scenarios to generate Q&A pairs with practical value

instructionGuide.title: Instruction Tuning Data Generation Guide
instructionGuide.taskClear: Task Clarity: Clearly describe the specific task to be executed, avoiding ambiguity
instructionGuide.actionable: Actionability: Instructions should be executable and specific with clear operational steps
instructionGuide.scenarioBased: Scenario-based: Design instructions based on practical application scenarios, close to real usage needs
instructionGuide.diversified: Diversified: Include different types and complexity levels of task instructions, covering multiple application scenarios
instructionGuide.scalable: Scalable: Instruction format should support decomposition and combination of complex tasks
instructionGuide.inputRelevance: Input Relevance: Input content should be highly relevant to instructions, providing necessary contextual information
instructionGuide.outputQuality: Output Quality: Provide high-quality output examples that meet expectations and reflect professional standards
instructionGuide.logicalConsistency: Logical Consistency: Ensure instruction-input-output triplets are logically consistent, forming complete task loops
instructionGuide.practicalValue: Practical Value: Output should have practical application value and solve real problems
instructionGuide.extractionSummary: Information extraction and summarization tasks: Extract key information from complex documents
instructionGuide.conversionFormatting: Content conversion and formatting tasks: Convert content between different formats
instructionGuide.analysisJudgment: Analysis and judgment tasks: Professional analysis based on given information
instructionGuide.creationGeneration: Creation and generation tasks: Generate new content based on requirements
instructionGuide.qaGuidance: Q&A and guidance tasks: Provide professional answers and guidance suggestions

classificationGuide.title: Text Classification Data Generation Guide
classificationGuide.representative: Representative: Select typical text segments that represent different categories
classificationGuide.appropriateLength: Appropriate Length: Text length suitable for classification tasks (recommended 100-300 characters)
classificationGuide.completeInfo: Complete Information: Ensure text segments contain sufficient classification feature information
classificationGuide.clearBoundaries: Clear Boundaries: Avoid vague or difficult-to-classify boundary cases
classificationGuide.categoryClarity: Category Clarity: Each label has clear definition and boundaries
classificationGuide.mutualExclusive: Mutual Exclusivity: Ensure categories are mutually exclusive, avoiding overlap
classificationGuide.balanced: Balanced: Try to maintain data balance among various categories
classificationGuide.practical: Practical: Labels should meet actual application needs
classificationGuide.samplesPerChunk: Extract 3-6 classification samples per document segment
classificationGuide.labelAccuracy: Ensure accuracy and consistency of labels
classificationGuide.positiveNegative: Include typical positive and negative examples

dialogueGuide.title: Dialogue Data Generation Guide
dialogueGuide.naturalFluent: Natural & Fluent: Dialogues should conform to natural language communication habits
dialogueGuide.contextCoherent: Context Coherent: Multi-turn dialogues maintain logical coherence
dialogueGuide.roleConsistent: Role Consistent: Maintain consistent role characteristics for dialogue participants
dialogueGuide.informationRich: Information Rich: Convey valuable information through dialogue
dialogueGuide.progressiveDisclosure: Progressive Disclosure: Gradually deepen topic exploration
dialogueGuide.intentUnderstanding: Intent Understanding: Accurately understand and respond to user needs
dialogueGuide.contextMemory: Context Memory: Maintain continuity of dialogue history
dialogueGuide.naturalTransition: Natural Transition: Topic transitions should be natural and reasonable
dialogueGuide.sequencesPerChunk: Generate 3-5 dialogue sequences per document segment
dialogueGuide.interactionRounds: Each dialogue contains 4-10 rounds of interaction
dialogueGuide.professionalAttitude: Reflect professional knowledge and service attitude

domainGuide.title: Domain Adaptation Data Generation Guide
domainGuide.professionalTerms: Professional Terms: Accurately use domain-related professional terminology and concepts
domainGuide.knowledgeDepth: Knowledge Depth: Reflect domain-specific knowledge depth and breadth
domainGuide.applicationScenarios: Application Scenarios: Combine with specific domain application scenarios and practical cases
domainGuide.professionalStandards: Professional Standards: Comply with industry norms and professional standards
domainGuide.conceptAssociation: Concept Association: Establish associative relationships between domain concepts
domainGuide.hierarchicalOrganization: Hierarchical Organization: Organize by knowledge difficulty and importance levels
domainGuide.theoryPractice: Theory-Practice Integration: Combine theoretical knowledge with practical applications
domainGuide.richCases: Rich Cases: Provide typical domain application cases and best practices
domainGuide.samplesPerChunk: Generate 4-7 domain-specialized samples per document segment
domainGuide.domainKnowledge: Highlight domain-specific knowledge points and core skills
domainGuide.proficiencyLevels: Include learning materials for different proficiency levels
domainGuide.latestTrends: Reflect latest trends and cutting-edge developments in the domain

reasoningGuide.title: Reasoning Data Generation Guide
reasoningGuide.clearSteps: Clear Steps: Each reasoning step should be clear and specific, easy to follow
reasoningGuide.logicalRigorous: Logical Rigor: Ensure logical consistency and rigor of the reasoning process
reasoningGuide.verifiable: Verifiable: Each step can be independently verified for correctness
reasoningGuide.completeness: Completeness: Complete reasoning chain from premise to conclusion, without skipping steps
reasoningGuide.explicitReasoning: Explicit Reasoning: Clearly display thinking process and decision basis
reasoningGuide.keyAssumptions: Key Assumptions: Explain key assumptions and conditions in reasoning
reasoningGuide.alternativeApproaches: Alternative Approaches: Consider other possible reasoning paths and solutions
reasoningGuide.uncertainty: Uncertainty: Appropriately express uncertainty and limitations in reasoning
reasoningGuide.deductiveReasoning: Deductive Reasoning: Logical derivation from general to specific
reasoningGuide.inductiveReasoning: Inductive Reasoning: Pattern summarization from specific to general
reasoningGuide.analogicalReasoning: Analogical Reasoning: Reasoning and analogical analysis based on similarity
reasoningGuide.causalReasoning: Causal Reasoning: Analyze cause-and-effect relationship chains
reasoningGuide.mathematicalReasoning: Mathematical Reasoning: Calculation and proof processes based on mathematical logic

distillationGuide.title: Knowledge Distillation Data Generation Guide
distillationGuide.coreConceptst: Core Concepts: Extract core knowledge points and key concepts from documents
distillationGuide.simplifiedExpression: Simplified Expression: Express complex concepts in simpler ways while maintaining comprehensibility
distillationGuide.fidelity: Fidelity: Ensure simplification does not lose original meaning, maintaining knowledge accuracy
distillationGuide.understandability: Understandability: Improve knowledge comprehensibility and memorability
distillationGuide.knowledgeHierarchy: Knowledge Hierarchy: Organize by importance and complexity levels
distillationGuide.dependencies: Dependencies: Clarify dependency relationships and logical order between knowledge points
distillationGuide.learningPath: Learning Path: Design reasonable learning sequence and progression routes
distillationGuide.difficultyGradient: Difficulty Gradient: Progressive arrangement from simple to complex
distillationGuide.keyInformation: Key Information: Highlight the most important information and core points
distillationGuide.redundancyElimination: Redundancy Elimination: Remove unnecessary repetitive content and redundant information
distillationGuide.structured: Structured: Organize knowledge in structured ways for easy understanding and memory
distillationGuide.easyRetrieval: Easy Retrieval: Convenient for quick search and application, improving usage efficiency
